cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.IR 

This paper deals with improving the semantic quality of word vectors, which is a common topic in natural language processing (NLP) and computational linguistics. The use of lexical resources and cross-lingual lexicons also suggests a focus on multilingual NLP. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also involves machine learning techniques, such as vector space models and dialogue state tracking, which could fall under cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The use of constraints and optimization methods may also relate to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
